Great kicked back location. We usually hit it at least once a week from our office for lunch. Fantastic Fish & Chips. Like fish not too deep fried with a heavy coating. The sweet potato chips are quite good, only complaint, no cole slaw...not that you need it with this hearty helping...but it is a routine I have gotten used to as a fish & chips fan. Burgers are disappointing as they are just average for the price. Good beer selection & the hot wings are fantastic! I haven't been on the weekend, but during the week it can become a busy place at lunch. Lots of TV's that make it look like a great place to catch the game.

